                        "name": "1.E.3 Number of members in non-profit organizations per 10 thous. population",
                      
                        "goal": "Goal 1. No poverty",
                      
                        "priority": "Development of social and solidarity economy",
                      
                        "definition": "Number of natural or legal persons associated with non-profit organisations (active associations and similar social organisations, foundations, social religious entities, economic and professional self-governments and employers' organisations).",
                      
                        "unit": "persons",
                      
                        "dimensions": "total",
                      
                        "methodology": "The non-profit sector is a group of entities that meet the following conditions:- are formalized to an appropriate degree (e.g. as a result of registration with the appropriate office), or at least their goals, method of operation and structure are of a permanent nature,- are institutionally separate from public administration,- are non-profit (they operate not for profit and do not distribute any surplus among their members, employees, etc.),- are self-governing (the authorities and directions of action are determined within the organization),- are characterized by voluntary participation in the organization's activities.Members of non-profit organizations are natural or legal persons (e.g. other organizations, business entities or institutions) associated in these organizations.",
                      
                        "source": "Statistics Poland",
                      
                        "availability": "Since 2014 data in two-year cycles",
                      
